status_message:
On the morning of Sept. 11, 2001, TIME's Nancy Gibbs got a phone call from our then-managing editor Jim Kelly. Gibbs was at home in Westchester, NY, away from the chaos filling Manhattan where the TIME offices are located. "He said, 'I wanted to know if you're game to write.' And I said, 'Of course. Which story do you want me to do? And he said, 'Well, I only want one story.'" 

Gibbs spent the next 36 hours writing the the cover story for TIME's special report on the events of 9/11, receiving nearly 1200 e-mails from the entire staff of TIME who hit the streets of New York to report for her. Here, you can watch her tell the story of how it all came together.
link_name: Behind the Scenes: TIME's Original 9/11 Cover Story

status_message:
It took one researcher four days to sift through an archive of more than 5,000 photo negatives to find this photo of Bill Clinton with Monica Lewinsky at a Democratic fund raiser in October 1996. 

Photographer Dirck Halstead credited his practice of preserving photos for the cover image, which TIME sat on for five months before using it to accompany the right story.

Read the cover story: http://ti.me/Hdc6sn
